HEADWORD: Sigmodont
<hw>Sig"mo*dont</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/
sigma (<?/) + <?/<?/<?/, <?/<?/<?/, a tooth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of a tribe (<fam>Sigmodontes</fam>) of rodents which
includes all the indigenous rats and mice of America. So called from the
form of the ridges of enamel on the crowns of the worn molars. Also used
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

